3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour using on-chain premium and interest rate components, with payments occurring precisely at each hour mark. The funding rate formula incorporates the 1-hour TWAP of the premium between perpetual and index prices, capped at ±0.75% per funding period. Since all order book operations occur on Hyperliquid's L1, funding rate calculations are transparent and verifiable on-chain, eliminating the opacity common in centralized exchanges. Position holders automatically receive or pay funding based on their long/short exposure, with settlements processed instantly through the native USDC margin system."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","SOL","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SOL/USDT represents one of the highest-volume perpetual pairs on Hyperliquid, providing sufficient liquidity for meaningful arbitrage positions without significant slippage. Solana's volatility and active DeFi ecosystem often create funding rate imbalances, especially during network upgrades or ecosystem developments. The 1-hour funding intervals on Hyperliquid, compared to 8-hour intervals on most exchanges, enable more frequent arbitrage opportunities and faster capital turnover for SOL positions."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"SOL/USDT funding rates on Hyperliquid typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per hour during normal market conditions, with extreme rates reaching ±0.75% during high volatility periods. During Solana ecosystem events like major DeFi launches or network upgrades, funding rates often skew positive as traders establish long positions to capture potential upside. The 1-hour intervals create more granular rate adjustments compared to traditional 8-hour cycles, resulting in rates that respond faster to market sentiment changes. Historical data shows funding rates tend to normalize more quickly on Hyperliquid due to the frequent reset intervals and the platform's efficient arbitrage environment."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategies"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange funding arbitrage between Hyperliquid and CEX platforms becomes profitable when rate differentials exceed the combined trading fees and transfer costs, typically around 0.15-0.2% threshold for SOL. The hourly funding cycles enable short-duration arbitrage strategies, where traders can capture rate differentials and exit positions before significant price movements occur. On-chain execution eliminates counterparty risk associated with centralized exchange custody, though it requires maintaining USDC liquidity on Hyperliquid L1. Advanced arbitrageurs often pair SOL perpetual positions with spot SOL holdings across multiple platforms to create delta-neutral funding collection strategies."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Management"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The primary risks include Hyperliquid's relatively short operational history compared to established CEXs, and the platform's dependence on its single L1 ecosystem. USDC-only margin requirements mean traders must manage stablecoin exposure and cannot use native SOL as collateral for leveraged positions. Network congestion or technical issues on Hyperliquid L1 could prevent timely position adjustments during volatile periods, though the platform's sub-second finality typically mitigates execution delays. The lack of KYC requirements provides operational flexibility but may limit access for institutional traders requiring compliance documentation."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are SOL/USDT funding rates updated on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding rates update every hour on Hyperliquid, with payments occurring precisely at the top of each hour UTC. This is more frequent than most exchanges which use 8-hour intervals, providing more arbitrage opportunities."},{"question":"What's the maximum funding rate for SOL perpetuals on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding rates are capped at ±0.75% per hour (±18% daily equivalent) to prevent extreme rate manipulation. During high volatility, rates approach these limits but the hourly resets help normalize them faster."},{"question":"Can I use SOL as collateral for perpetual trading on Hyperliquid?","answer":"No, Hyperliquid only accepts USDC as margin collateral. Traders must convert SOL to USDC before opening perpetual positions, which adds an additional currency risk component to consider."},{"question":"How does Hyperliquid's on-chain order book affect SOL funding rates?","answer":"The fully on-chain order book provides transparent price discovery and funding rate calculations that are verifiable on Hyperliquid L1. This transparency can lead to more efficient funding rate discovery compared to centralized exchanges with opaque calculations."}]}]
